article.headline: W. Illinois 77, UMKC 62
article.story: MACOMB, Ill. (AP) -- David Jackson and Jerryck Owens-Murrey each scored 16 points to lead Western Illinois to a 77-62 win over Missouri-Kansas City on Thursday night. Jackson's free throw with 9:26 left in the first half put Western Illinois (10-11, 5-5 Summit League) ahead for good 18-17 and sparked a 15-1 run for the Leathernecks. David DuBois added 14 points and Chris Gonzalez and Josh Rivers each chipped in 11 points for Western Illinois, which led 39-24 at the half. Tim Blackwell had a game-high 17 points and Dane Brumagin added 13 for Missouri-Kansas City (8-15, 3-7), which couldn't come back from a poor shooting first half. The Kangaroos were 9-for-27 from field-goal range (33.3 percent), compared with 15-for-28 (53.6 percent) for the Leathernecks.
